# ION-DEX UI Engineering Harness Protocol v3.0
# Auto-loaded by Cursor — DO NOT MODIFY without Master approval

## Architecture
- DesignTokens: Single source of truth for all visual attributes
- DEXGridHarness: 12-col grid, repeat(12, 1fr)
- NeonCard: Foundation component for all modules
- agent_harness.py: Contract compile/test/audit gateway

## 1. Vision Protocol
- NO HARDCODING: Never use hex/rgba colors, pixel margins, or padding directly
- TOKEN USAGE: All visual attributes from `src/lib/design-tokens.ts`
- GRID ENFORCEMENT: All layouts use DEXGridHarness, grid-column: span X
- ASSET INTEGRITY: .webp assets from /public/assets/icons/, no CSS-drawn graphics

## 2. Backend Protocol
- AGENT HARNESS: All contract ops through agent_harness.py
- NO MOCKS: Real Blueprint test suite, no mocked blockchain states
- SECURITY FIRST: Gas-limit checks + consistent error handling

## 3. Workflow (3-Step)
1. ANALYSIS: State Grid coordinates and tokens before coding
2. EXECUTION: Reference only provided architectural components
3. VERIFICATION: Self-check against protocol

## 4. Visual Red Line
- AI MUST proactively flag visible deviations BEFORE user points them out
- "Close enough" = NOT acceptable. Every pixel deviation is a bug.

## 5. Asset Quality Gate
- HD WebP, transparent background, uniform padding at export
- Jagged edges / non-transparent = UNUSABLE, must re-export
- AI MUST alert immediately if icon quality is insufficient
